  "text": "A marginally bound state exists whenever the string web is irreducible, as anticipated in [CITATION_1] , namely when a generic web cannot be decomposed into sub-webs. Thus we find sites on the charge lattice which are occupied by marginally bound states, but it is not clear whether, in general, other sites are occupied.",
